If you have two strong characters that the audience can identify with and both are evenly matched or the underdog takes the lead kind of thing...it's usually cool<br>
the brazilian grand prix is a good example....<br>
Barichello racing in ferrari's old car (on a light fuel load)....charged from about midway in the pack to first place in only a couple laps.....he ended up running out of gas (no I don't believe it was hydraulic failure)...<br>
then it was michael shumacher vs Ralf shumacher for 1st place....the win pretty much rested on pit strategy....and a great game of catch up...it was a great race....michael was faster in the straits and ralf faster in the corners...<br>
barichello was the underdog....a very skilled driver...but in an older car...<br>
ralf and michael are brothers....on different teams...both are incredibly skilled...both were in great cars just going for different strategies...<br>
I don't see what people get from nascar<br>
the WRC race was on just after...I won't get into that <p><pre>
